This comes amid escalating US-EU tensions, including a US visa ban on five Europeans accused of online censorship and Trump's threat of substantial tariffs on countries enacting digital taxes.
title: US-Europe visa & trade war shows no end: European Commission named in Google filing; what it means

author: TNN
description: A passenger bus veered off the road and plunged into a deep gorge near Sailapani in Almora district on Tuesday, killing at least six people and injuring several others. The bus was traveling from Dwarahat to Ramnagar when the accident occurred, prompting a large-scale rescue operation amidst challenging terrain.
title: Uttarakhand accident: 6 dead, several injured as bus falls into gorge in Almora

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Snakes entering toilets are rare, driven by a search for shelter, moisture, or escape from flooding. They follow prey like rodents and insects into underground pipes, with toilets serving as accidental exits. While unsettling, these encounters are not planned attacks. Simple home maintenance can significantly reduce the already low risk.
title: What attracts snakes to emerge from toilet bowls?

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Billionaire Kumar Mangalam Birla recently graced 'Kaun Banega Crorepati 17,' highlighting his influential family. His wife, Neerja, is a dedicated philanthropist and education trust chairperson. Their children, musician Ananya, psychology student Advaitesha championing women's health, and former cricketer Aryaman now managing businesses, have all carved their own successful paths, earning their father's immense pride.
title: Who is Kumar Mangalam Birla? Meet ‘KBC 17’ contestant, wife Neerja, & children

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: An alleged ISIS sympathizer, 21-year-old John Michael Garza Jr., was arrested in Texas by the FBI. He is accused of attempting to provide bomb-making components and cryptocurrency to individuals he believed were acting for the terrorist group. Garza allegedly shared ISIS propaganda and offered instructions for building explosive devices.
title: 'Radical Islamic terrorism': FBI arrests 'ISIS sympathiser'; attempted to provide explosives

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Stephen Curry's son, Canon, showcased remarkable dribbling skills during a Warriors game. The view captivated fans and the clip went viral. Comparisons to 'The Lion King's' Simba emerged, with many predicting a bright future for the young prodigy.  Canon, the youngest of Stephen and Ayesha Curry's four children, is already impressing with his talent.
title: Stephen Curry’s son Canon stuns fans with impressive dribbling skills

author: TNN
description: Uttar Pradesh Congress chief Ajay Rai condemned the harassment of Japanese tourists in Varanasi, calling it shameful and a reflection of deteriorating law and order. He highlighted the incident in the Prime Minister's constituency as a sign of growing lawlessness and mob culture, urging a high-level investigation and strict action to protect tourists and India's reputation.
title: Watch: Japanese tourists 'harassed' by locals at Varanasi ghat

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: America's President Donald Trump has issued a stern warning to Iran. He stated that Iran will face severe repercussions if it attempts to revive its missile program. This comes amid reports of Iran potentially rebuilding its ballistic missile capabilities at new locations. Iran's advisor countered, vowing a strong response to any aggression. The US had previously targeted Iranian nuclear sites.
title: ‘We will knock them down’: Trump draws red line on Iran’s missile programme; Tehran fires back with warning

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Young wicketkeeper-batter Dhruv Jurel has made a compelling case for India's ODI squad with exceptional Vijay Hazare Trophy performances.  His recent unbeaten 160 off 101 balls, alongside over 300 runs in three matches, puts him firmly in contention for the upcoming New Zealand series, especially with Rishabh Pant's potential absence.
title: 160 not out! Jurel knocks on ODI door: VHT blitz puts selectors on notice ahead of NZ series

author: DEVANSHI MEHTA
description: An Air India Express pilot, Captain Virender Sejwal, has been arrested for allegedly assaulting a passenger at Delhi's IGI Airport. The incident, which occurred on December 19, involved an altercation at a staff entry gate. The passenger, Ankit Dewan, later shared his experience on social media, leading to a government-ordered probe and the pilot being grounded.
title: Delhi airport assault: Air India Express Pilot arrested weeks after thrashing passenger

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Saudi Arabia bombed Yemen's Mukalla port, targeting UAE-supplied weapons for separatists. This strike escalates tensions between Riyadh and Abu Dhabi, who back opposing factions in Yemen's war. The attack follows recent Saudi warnings to separatists to halt advances, highlighting growing friction between the Gulf allies over regional influence.
title: 'Limited military op': Saudi bombs Yemeni port; targets alleged arms shipment arrived from UAE

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, opened in red on Tuesday on weak global cues. While Nifty50 went below 25,950, BSE Sensex was down over 120 points.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens below 25,950; BSE Sensex down over 100 points

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Indian selectors have dropped Shubman Gill from the 2026 T20 World Cup squad, citing his recent form slump. Despite this, former spinner Harbhajan Singh believes it's not an end for Gill, highlighting the intense competition. Suryakumar Yadav retains captaincy, with selectors backing his ability to deliver. Axar Patel is vice-captain, and Ishan Kishan returns.
title: T20 World Cup snub: 'It's not the end of the road' — ex-India spinner backs Shubman Gill

author: CH SUSHIL RAO AND SHIVA KUMAR PINNA
description: Two childhood friends from Telangana, Meghana Rani Pullakhandam (25) and Bhavana Kadiyala (24), tragically died in a road accident in Bishop, California on Sunday. The duo, who had completed their master's degrees in computer science in Ohio, were on a trip when their car veered off the road and fell into a gorge.
title: 'We're heartbroken': 2 Telangana friends die in California accident; family urges repatriation

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Former Bangladesh Prime Minister and BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia has died at the age of 80. A dominant political figure for decades and the country's first woman prime minister, Zia had been battling multiple serious health complications. Her death occurs as Bangladesh approaches crucial national elections.
title: Who was Khaleda Zia? Bangladesh’s first woman PM; archrival of Sheikh Hasina

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Mac users can easily capture screenshots and record their screens using the built-in Screenshot panel, accessible via Shift + Command + 5. This tool allows for capturing the entire screen, specific windows, or selected areas, with options for timers, audio, and mouse pointer visibility. Customization of settings and file formats further streamlines the process.
title: MacOS screenshot guide: Easy steps, keyboard shortcuts and settings; supported file formats explained

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump and Prime Minister Netanyahu met at Mar-a-Lago, presenting a united front but revealing no concrete progress on the Gaza ceasefire's second phase. Trump made some contested claims about potential pardon for Netanyahu, which Israel's presidency disputed, whereas he also went on to issue warnings for Hamas and Iran.
title: 'Big discussion on West Bank': What went down at Trump & Netanyahu's meeting; key takeaways

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi started its day on Tuesday shrouded in heavy fog, which severely impaired visibility and created chaotic traffic conditions. The air quality dropped to alarming levels, reaching both 'very poor' and 'severe' status.
title: Delhi air pollution: At 390, city's AQI in ‘very poor’ category; dense fog reduces visibility

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) chairperson and former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia has died at the age of 80. A dominant political figure for decades, Zia had been in critical condition for months. She served as prime minister twice, first becoming the nation's first female premier in 1991.
title: Bangladesh: Former PM & BNP chairman Khaleda Zia passes away at 80

author: LACHIT ROY
description: Anthony Joshua is recovering in hospital after a fatal road crash in Nigeria claimed the lives of two of his closest friends, Latif Ayodele and Sina Ghami. The pair were integral members of his team, serving as personal trainer and strength coach. Joshua survived the collision and remains in a stable condition as investigations continue.
title: Who were Latif Ayodele and Sina Ghami? Tragedy strikes Anthony Joshua

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Jeff Bezos welcomed former ULA CEO Tory Bruno to Blue Origin's newly formed National Security Group. Bruno will lead the group, reporting to CEO Dave Limp. Bezos' rare social media post included Blue Origin's motto, "Gradatim Ferociter," meaning "Step by Step, Ferociously," reflecting his approach to spaceflight.
title: Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin leadership update: Amazon founder welcomes executive

author: RICHA PINTO AND AHMED ALI
description: Bhandup West faced a devastating tragedy when a BEST bus driver, during a U-turn, lost control, resulting in the tragic deaths of four individuals and injuries to fourteen pedestrians. The electric AC bus careened off the road, striking a pole before impacting innocent bystanders.
title: 2 Mondays, a year apart: BEST bus mows down 4, injures 14 in Mumbai; driver suspended

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US forces killed two suspected "male narco-terrorists" in a strike on an alleged drug-smuggling boat in the Eastern Pacific. This brings the total killed in Washington's campaign to at least 107. The military claims intelligence confirmed the vessel's involvement in drug trafficking, though evidence for the strikes remains unprovided, sparking debate over legality.
title: Another US strike, two more dead: Anti-drug campaign toll crosses 100 — watch

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Dhurandhar, the spy-thriller starring Ranveer Singh and Akshaye Khanna, is a massive box office success. The film has crossed Rs 701 crore in India and Rs 1078 crore worldwide. It has surpassed Kalki 2898 AD and Pathaan in collections. Dhurandhar is now chasing Jawan's lifetime earnings and is set to become the biggest Bollywood grosser.
title: 'Dhurandhar' BO collection Day 25: Ranveer Singh starrer scores Rs 1078 crore worldwide haul

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: As Indian airlines face a dwindling pool of pilots due to updated flight duty regulations, IndiGo and Air India are ramping up their recruitment efforts. IndiGo, in particular, is set to hire 100 new pilots this January, with captains receiving enticing signing bonuses that could soar to ₹50 lakh.
title: 'Where are the captains?': AI, IndiGo in dogfight for pilots; joining bonus up to Rs 50 lakh

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: A tech firm, SmarTek21, is suing its advisor, TGP GP Management, alleging it was misled into a $5.2 million acquisition of IT Avalon. SmarTek21 claims TGP rushed the deal despite concerns about IT Avalon's finances, which have since required significant cash infusions. TGP, however, denies the allegations, asserting thorough due diligence and a strong business outlook for the combined entity.
title: Deal gone wrong: US tech company drags acquisition adviser to court; alleges fee-driven bad advice

description: Mandhana’s run-scoring at the top of the order has played a key role in India Women’s results this season. She has scored runs in different formats and conditions while setting up innings for the team.
title: Just 62 runs away: Smriti Mandhana set to surpass Shubman Gill; this record in sight

title: 'Next one won't come': Mandhana's warning; cautions against living off past success
